Q 1:Why String is immutable in java and?
Ans=  String is immutable in java because of the following reasons
#Synchronsie
#concurrency
#security
#class loading
#un authorised access

Q no 2: what is the difference between String and String Builder?
String is immutable , we cant change the value inside String.
But in String  Builder class we can change the value inside of string.

